1
00:00:05,771 --> 00:00:07,371
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,441 --> 00:00:09,181
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,211 --> 00:00:12,011
- Unbelievable.
- Is Dae Han's girlfriend...

4
00:00:12,681 --> 00:00:13,781
Dong Suk?

5
00:00:18,181 --> 00:00:19,191
Mom.

6
00:00:26,531 --> 00:00:27,531
Answer me.

7
00:00:28,331 --> 00:00:29,731
The person you're dating...

8
00:00:30,331 --> 00:00:32,201
Is it Dong Suk, Dr. Yang's sister?

9
00:00:35,941 --> 00:00:37,441
Yes. That's right, Mom.

10
00:00:39,641 --> 00:00:41,911
How on earth could you do this?

11
00:00:42,681 --> 00:00:44,911
- Oh, no...
- Mother, please.

12
00:00:46,411 --> 00:00:48,751
- Yes, I'm dating Dong Suk.
- You fool!

13
00:00:48,821 --> 00:00:51,151
- You can't, absolutely not!
- Mom, please just listen to me.

14
00:00:51,221 --> 00:00:54,951
- Will you just stop it already?
- Mom, please, just hear me out.

15
00:00:56,391 --> 00:00:57,521
Seong Mi, let's go inside.

16
00:00:59,431 --> 00:01:01,131
- But...
- Mom.

17
00:01:01,391 --> 00:01:02,401
Mom!

18
00:01:02,401 --> 00:01:05,201
My gosh. Dae Han, let's talk inside.

19
00:01:05,931 --> 00:01:07,301
You too, honey. Come on.

20
00:01:08,401 --> 00:01:09,401
Come on.

21
00:01:16,741 --> 00:01:18,111
You said she had a child...

22
00:01:19,251 --> 00:01:20,581
You meant Dong Suk?

23
00:01:22,451 --> 00:01:23,551
Yes.

24
00:01:23,921 --> 00:01:26,691
I think
they were there for each other...

25
00:01:26,751 --> 00:01:28,821
and ended up
developing feelings, Mother.

26
00:01:28,821 --> 00:01:30,291
Don't you dare take his side.

27
00:01:30,821 --> 00:01:32,331
Why are you getting involved?

28
00:01:33,031 --> 00:01:35,701
- Is this any of your business?
- And you think it's not?

29
00:01:36,001 --> 00:01:38,301
- Am I a stranger to you?
- Even a stranger wouldn't do this.

30
00:01:38,931 --> 00:01:40,571
I'm sorry, Mom, Seong Mi.

31
00:01:41,931 --> 00:01:43,301
But I can't break up with Dong Suk.

32
00:01:44,271 --> 00:01:46,511
I can't live a day without her...
No, actually,

33
00:01:47,441 --> 00:01:48,841
I can't live for a single second
without her.

34
00:01:49,111 --> 00:01:50,441
Dae Han...

35
00:01:50,881 --> 00:01:51,881
You punk.

36
00:01:52,311 --> 00:01:54,651
You got a divorce
because of Dong Suk's ex-husband.

37
00:01:54,951 --> 00:01:58,081
Bucket made a huge scene over it.
Have you forgotten already?

38
00:01:58,351 --> 00:02:00,891
- Are you out of your mind?
- Yes.

39
00:02:01,491 --> 00:02:02,521
I am.

40
00:02:02,961 --> 00:02:04,221
I'm crazy in love.
You got a problem with that?

41
00:02:04,521 --> 00:02:05,531
Why, you...

42
00:02:05,761 --> 00:02:07,031
Did you ever think...

43
00:02:08,031 --> 00:02:09,101
about your mother in all this?

44
00:02:09,401 --> 00:02:12,301
I did, Mom. Of course, I did.
I've thought about it a lot.

45
00:02:12,501 --> 00:02:15,871
But Mom, you've spent 30 years
hating and resenting them.

46
00:02:15,871 --> 00:02:17,471
Don't you think
it's finally time to stop?

47
00:02:18,871 --> 00:02:23,541
- So I should just put up with it?
- That's not what I meant.

48
00:02:24,181 --> 00:02:26,411
You've reconciled,
so I honestly thought...

49
00:02:26,581 --> 00:02:27,911
Seong Mi,
you should get ready for bed.

50
00:02:28,411 --> 00:02:29,581
She came home
from the hospital yesterday,

51
00:02:29,581 --> 00:02:31,081
so we shouldn't stress her out.

52
00:02:36,191 --> 00:02:37,261
I'm sorry, Seong Mi.

53
00:02:37,591 --> 00:02:39,261
Give me a break with your "sorry."

54
00:02:39,591 --> 00:02:41,231
- You little...
- Let's go to our room.

55
00:02:41,291 --> 00:02:43,431
- You've lost your mind. Seriously.
- Go inside.

56
00:02:43,501 --> 00:02:44,501
I swear, that guy...

57
00:02:51,841 --> 00:02:53,341
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

58
00:02:53,411 --> 00:02:54,411
Woo Jae.

59
00:02:55,441 --> 00:02:56,481
Was it busy?

60
00:02:57,281 --> 00:02:58,311
A little.

61
00:02:58,581 --> 00:03:01,511
- They all just left.
- Sorry, that must've been tough.

62
00:03:02,181 --> 00:03:04,221
It's okay. Eun Bin helped out a lot.

63
00:03:07,051 --> 00:03:08,051
Woo Jae.

64
00:03:08,321 --> 00:03:09,321
Yes?

65
00:03:10,221 --> 00:03:11,821
I broke up with your uncle.

66
00:03:15,391 --> 00:03:17,701
He's probably having a hard time.

67
00:03:18,831 --> 00:03:20,531
Can you look out for him for me?

68
00:03:21,801 --> 00:03:22,801
Okay.

69
00:03:25,541 --> 00:03:27,011
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

70
00:03:30,441 --> 00:03:33,711
Aunt Dong Suk, what happened?
What did Grandpa and Dad say?

71
00:03:33,881 --> 00:03:37,451
If you knew about Min Seo,
you should have told me.

72
00:03:37,721 --> 00:03:39,021
I'm asking you what happened!

73
00:03:39,451 --> 00:03:42,861
What do you think?
They were all a bit shocked,

74
00:03:43,421 --> 00:03:44,721
but they took it well.

75
00:03:46,361 --> 00:03:47,431
Oh, well...

76
00:03:47,531 --> 00:03:48,531
That's a relief.

77
00:03:49,131 --> 00:03:51,261
What a strange twist of fate.

78
00:03:51,701 --> 00:03:53,371
I can't believe
Min Seo is Se Ri's daughter.

79
00:03:54,431 --> 00:03:55,801
What are you talking about?

80
00:03:56,671 --> 00:03:57,941
Oh, well...

81
00:03:58,271 --> 00:03:59,611
Is it okay to tell him?

82
00:04:00,541 --> 00:04:02,911
It's not like it's a secret
or anything bad.

83
00:04:03,741 --> 00:04:07,211
Se Ri had a daughter she gave up
for adoption before she got married,

84
00:04:07,611 --> 00:04:08,651
and it turns out that was Min Seo.

85
00:04:09,581 --> 00:04:10,651
Seriously?

86
00:04:10,921 --> 00:04:12,051
Yes, for real.

87
00:04:13,921 --> 00:04:17,361
She said she wanted to find someone
in Korea. It was her mom.

88
00:04:18,191 --> 00:04:19,361
That's right. Well...

89
00:04:19,661 --> 00:04:22,361
You two keep talking.
I should get going.

90
00:04:22,431 --> 00:04:24,431
- I'm going home, Auntie.
- Okay.

91
00:04:24,431 --> 00:04:25,431
Wait...

92
00:04:29,401 --> 00:04:30,841
You weren't too shocked?

93
00:04:33,041 --> 00:04:36,211
Not shocked? Are you kidding?
I almost had a heart attack.

94
00:04:37,411 --> 00:04:39,051
You didn't show it at all.

95
00:04:39,881 --> 00:04:42,181
When did you find out?

96
00:04:42,781 --> 00:04:44,181
Not too long ago.

97
00:04:44,981 --> 00:04:46,351
Eun Bin found out first.

98
00:04:47,191 --> 00:04:49,921
Eun Bin really stepped up this time.

99
00:04:50,621 --> 00:04:54,031
I know. She always acted like a kid,
but she's really grown up.

100
00:04:54,431 --> 00:04:55,701
So when are you leaving?

101
00:04:56,031 --> 00:04:57,761
After the adoption is finalized.

102
00:04:59,571 --> 00:05:01,671
I thought you'd get married
and settle down here,

103
00:05:02,001 --> 00:05:03,401
but you're still determined to go?

104
00:05:04,171 --> 00:05:05,171
Yes.

105
00:05:05,441 --> 00:05:09,311
Still, I'm glad things ended well
before I leave.

106
00:05:12,481 --> 00:05:16,051
You have another granddaughter now,
so please take good care of her.

107
00:05:16,851 --> 00:05:19,091
Of course.
She's Se Ri's daughter, after all.

108
00:05:23,191 --> 00:05:25,621
No, Se Ri. It's...

109
00:05:25,831 --> 00:05:27,761
I can explain everything. Okay?

110
00:05:29,101 --> 00:05:32,001
It's just that...
Kang Hyeon Cheol's phone number...

111
00:05:32,131 --> 00:05:37,001
You saved it as "Ms. Jo Hyeon Suk,"
so I thought you were cheating.

112
00:05:37,071 --> 00:05:38,271
Wouldn't you?

113
00:05:40,211 --> 00:05:43,181
(Application for Divorce
by Mutual Consent)

114
00:05:43,381 --> 00:05:44,381
So...

115
00:05:46,411 --> 00:05:49,151
You were gathering evidence
to divorce me?

116
00:05:50,121 --> 00:05:52,151
And that's how you found out
about Min Seo?

117
00:05:53,151 --> 00:05:55,721
No! What are you talking about?
A divorce?

118
00:05:57,061 --> 00:05:59,591
This was... The private detective...

119
00:06:01,991 --> 00:06:03,301
I had no idea.

120
00:06:03,631 --> 00:06:07,131
That guy said if I were
to get a divorce, I'd need this,

121
00:06:07,201 --> 00:06:10,701
and then he shoved it in
without asking. You see?

122
00:06:11,201 --> 00:06:13,011
Hiding my past when I married you...

123
00:06:14,411 --> 00:06:15,471
That's right.

124
00:06:16,441 --> 00:06:18,141
It's grounds for divorce.

125
00:06:19,181 --> 00:06:20,511
And yet,

126
00:06:21,851 --> 00:06:24,751
I was so incredibly grateful
that you were so understanding.

127
00:06:26,291 --> 00:06:29,061
It felt like you were finally
starting to truly trust me,

128
00:06:30,921 --> 00:06:32,891
and I was just so happy about it.

129
00:06:33,591 --> 00:06:35,761
No, Se Ri, I do trust you!
Please, Se Ri.

130
00:06:36,661 --> 00:06:38,761
After living with me for 16 years,

131
00:06:39,631 --> 00:06:42,001
if you had questions,
you could have asked me directly.

132
00:06:43,171 --> 00:06:44,471
How could you possibly...

133
00:06:46,041 --> 00:06:49,081
hire a private detective
to look into me like this, honey?

134
00:06:49,611 --> 00:06:50,611
I can't believe...

135
00:06:51,011 --> 00:06:52,011
Se Ri.

136
00:06:52,751 --> 00:06:54,451
Se Ri, I'm sorry. Please, Se Ri!

137
00:06:54,911 --> 00:06:57,181
- Mother?
- Se Ri, I'm sorry. Don't cry, okay?

138
00:06:57,181 --> 00:07:00,751
- What's going on?
- Dad, what's happening? Dad!

139
00:07:01,151 --> 00:07:04,691
- Se Ri found out everything.
- Found out what?

140
00:07:04,861 --> 00:07:06,661
That I hired a private investigator
to look into her.

141
00:07:07,761 --> 00:07:08,931
I'll go check on her.

142
00:07:09,531 --> 00:07:11,361
What are you talking about?
A private detective?

143
00:07:11,901 --> 00:07:13,871
You see, Dad...

144
00:07:16,901 --> 00:07:18,441
- Let's hurry.
- Okay!

145
00:07:19,271 --> 00:07:20,711
What? Mom!

146
00:07:22,681 --> 00:07:24,541
- What's going on? Hyun Bin!
- What?

147
00:07:26,251 --> 00:07:27,251
What's happening?

148
00:07:27,681 --> 00:07:31,081
I thought the talk went well.
Did something happen?

149
00:07:34,851 --> 00:07:35,861
At first,

150
00:07:36,591 --> 00:07:38,321
I thought Se Ri was cheating on me,

151
00:07:38,761 --> 00:07:40,761
so I started looking into it.
Then I found out she had a daughter,

152
00:07:41,261 --> 00:07:42,531
and that the daughter was living
in our house.

153
00:07:43,031 --> 00:07:44,961
Then I thought
she married me for money...

154
00:07:44,961 --> 00:07:46,301
to give her daughter a cut.

155
00:07:46,371 --> 00:07:47,701
That's the idea
that got into my head.

156
00:07:48,371 --> 00:07:52,911
What fortune was she after?
You had nothing before marrying her.

157
00:07:53,271 --> 00:07:56,841
She helped you build everything
you have now.

158
00:07:57,481 --> 00:08:01,711
It's natural for a parent
to want to provide for their child.

159
00:08:01,781 --> 00:08:03,421
What's so wrong with that?

160
00:08:04,381 --> 00:08:06,951
- I'm sorry, Dad.
- You're pathetic.

161
00:08:07,221 --> 00:08:09,861
How can you still think that way?

162
00:08:10,561 --> 00:08:11,621
You hired a private detective?
Unbelievable.

163
00:08:16,331 --> 00:08:20,971
- I swear, my dad is impossible.
- What are we going to do?

164
00:08:21,231 --> 00:08:22,941
What if this drives a wedge
between them?

165
00:08:34,351 --> 00:08:36,781
This is the first time
I've ever seen you drink.

166
00:08:39,751 --> 00:08:40,821
I used to drink years ago,

167
00:08:42,451 --> 00:08:45,321
especially after giving Min Seo up
for adoption.

168
00:08:47,291 --> 00:08:48,591
I felt like I kept seeing her
everywhere I looked.

169
00:08:49,901 --> 00:08:51,961
It was absolutely unbearable.

170
00:08:53,831 --> 00:08:55,731
I just wanted her
to grow up happy...

171
00:08:57,001 --> 00:08:59,871
in a good home, so I sent her away.

172
00:09:01,471 --> 00:09:03,141
But after she was gone,

173
00:09:05,041 --> 00:09:06,781
I just didn't want to live anymore.

174
00:09:09,621 --> 00:09:11,081
That's when your father...

175
00:09:12,281 --> 00:09:14,121
asked me to live with him.

176
00:09:16,821 --> 00:09:18,761
He said we should live together.

177
00:09:21,191 --> 00:09:23,531
This giant of a man...

178
00:09:24,131 --> 00:09:26,571
with his palms sweating nervously...

179
00:09:29,201 --> 00:09:31,871
shyly asked me to live with him.

180
00:09:33,711 --> 00:09:35,411
It made me feel so secure.

181
00:09:38,781 --> 00:09:41,551
Then he showed me
a picture of you...

182
00:09:42,511 --> 00:09:44,381
and Eun Bin...

183
00:09:45,421 --> 00:09:48,651
and told me his father
lived with him, too.

184
00:09:50,421 --> 00:09:52,161
That's quite the move.

185
00:09:53,831 --> 00:09:54,831
It was.

186
00:09:56,401 --> 00:09:57,931
And that's why I came here.

187
00:09:59,901 --> 00:10:00,901
To his house.

188
00:10:02,471 --> 00:10:04,601
There were many people
for me to love,

189
00:10:06,741 --> 00:10:08,871
and I was just so happy.

190
00:10:13,551 --> 00:10:15,851
If I had told him about Min Seo
back then,

191
00:10:18,681 --> 00:10:20,991
do you think he would still have
asked me to live with him?

192
00:10:23,621 --> 00:10:26,531
Knowing that he despises women
who abandon their children,

193
00:10:28,731 --> 00:10:30,401
I just couldn't bring myself
to say it.

194
00:10:34,271 --> 00:10:36,001
So yes,
I hid it from him on purpose,

195
00:10:37,201 --> 00:10:39,071
which is grounds for divorce.

196
00:10:40,941 --> 00:10:43,381
- What do you mean, divorce?
- I...

197
00:10:44,241 --> 00:10:45,641
I wasn't good to you kids...

198
00:10:46,881 --> 00:10:48,781
because I wanted something
from this family.

199
00:10:50,051 --> 00:10:51,051
I...

200
00:10:52,081 --> 00:10:53,221
Our family...

201
00:10:55,351 --> 00:10:57,491
I truly love you all so much,
Hyun Bin.

202
00:10:59,461 --> 00:11:00,531
I know.

203
00:11:02,091 --> 00:11:03,101
But...

204
00:11:06,701 --> 00:11:08,601
I don't think he loves me.

205
00:11:28,921 --> 00:11:31,361
You two should talk.

206
00:11:31,421 --> 00:11:33,891
I'll just be going now.

207
00:11:42,841 --> 00:11:44,341
I heard my brother said
something to you.

208
00:11:45,801 --> 00:11:47,611
I should've stopped him. I'm sorry.

209
00:11:48,171 --> 00:11:49,781
What do you have to be sorry for?

210
00:11:50,541 --> 00:11:52,311
I'm the one who said
we should break up.

211
00:11:52,981 --> 00:11:54,411
I can't break up with you.

212
00:11:55,251 --> 00:11:56,721
I'm never letting you go.

213
00:12:02,251 --> 00:12:03,761
Your father...

214
00:12:04,291 --> 00:12:06,831
I heard he texted your brother
to stop looking for him.

215
00:12:08,431 --> 00:12:09,431
Yes.

216
00:12:09,831 --> 00:12:11,561
I suppose that means
my mom and your dad...

217
00:12:12,601 --> 00:12:14,601
are still getting along fine.

218
00:12:17,001 --> 00:12:18,701
So for us to be dating...

219
00:12:19,671 --> 00:12:21,271
It feels completely wrong.

220
00:12:22,411 --> 00:12:23,941
So you're really breaking up
with me?

221
00:12:26,081 --> 00:12:30,121
Yes. I really can't do this anymore.

222
00:12:33,221 --> 00:12:34,221
I'm sorry.

223
00:12:46,701 --> 00:12:47,701
Ju Ah!

224
00:12:51,641 --> 00:12:52,641
What's wrong?

225
00:12:53,141 --> 00:12:55,371
Are you crying?
Wait, have you been crying?

226
00:12:55,671 --> 00:13:00,151
- No.
- Why is a grown woman crying?

227
00:13:00,611 --> 00:13:04,351
Gosh, once I start crying,
I can't stop. What should I do?

228
00:13:04,451 --> 00:13:06,121
I have to think of something else.
Anything else.

229
00:13:07,691 --> 00:13:09,961
Want me to tell you something
to take your mind off it?

230
00:13:11,591 --> 00:13:13,761
Why? What's going on?

231
00:13:15,391 --> 00:13:17,901
Apparently,
Hyun Bin has a new sister.

232
00:13:18,561 --> 00:13:19,571
A new sister?

233
00:13:20,271 --> 00:13:24,541
- Is his stepmom pregnant?
- No, that's not it.

234
00:13:25,371 --> 00:13:28,141
You know that friend I worked with
at the barbecue place?

235
00:13:28,311 --> 00:13:30,481
She's actually Eun Bin's stepmom's
biological daughter.

236
00:13:31,681 --> 00:13:35,911
Really? So she had a kid of her own?

237
00:13:35,981 --> 00:13:38,581
Yes. She gave her up for adoption
a long time ago,

238
00:13:38,651 --> 00:13:40,091
and it looks like
they just reconnected.

239
00:13:40,721 --> 00:13:44,591
So that's what Director Yang meant
by a family issue.

240
00:13:48,231 --> 00:13:49,261
Hey, Uncle.

241
00:13:51,731 --> 00:13:53,071
Right now?

242
00:13:57,341 --> 00:14:00,771
I was just going to have a drink
with Woo Jae,

243
00:14:01,571 --> 00:14:03,241
but I'm glad my Ju Ah
could make it, too.

244
00:14:05,211 --> 00:14:06,211
Uncle.

245
00:14:07,011 --> 00:14:09,411
She knows the whole story, Uncle.

246
00:14:15,221 --> 00:14:16,221
I see.

247
00:14:16,521 --> 00:14:17,691
Uncle.

248
00:14:18,721 --> 00:14:19,931
I'm not breaking up with her.

249
00:14:20,461 --> 00:14:22,931
You know you can't be together,
Uncle.

250
00:14:23,601 --> 00:14:27,231
Knowing that doesn't make it easy
to control your heart.

251
00:14:29,471 --> 00:14:30,871
Yes, that's true.

252
00:14:34,811 --> 00:14:37,481
I'm just glad you two understand.

253
00:14:57,631 --> 00:14:58,761
We're home.

254
00:14:59,131 --> 00:15:00,771
Oh, how come you're all together?

255
00:15:00,931 --> 00:15:03,641
We ran into each other out front
and just had one quick drink.

256
00:15:05,271 --> 00:15:07,241
Way to go, Gong Dae Han.

257
00:15:07,571 --> 00:15:11,681
Knowing your sister-in-law is ill,
you turned the family upside down.

258
00:15:12,011 --> 00:15:13,981
Now, you're dragging your niece
and nephew out for drinks?

259
00:15:15,751 --> 00:15:17,581
What gives you the right
to glare at me?

260
00:15:18,251 --> 00:15:19,251
Apologize.

261
00:15:19,721 --> 00:15:21,821
- What?
- Uncle.

262
00:15:22,391 --> 00:15:23,661
Apologize to me.

263
00:15:23,961 --> 00:15:25,861
Apologize for what, you punk?
For what?

264
00:15:26,161 --> 00:15:28,261
For meeting Dong Suk
and telling her to break up with me.

265
00:15:28,761 --> 00:15:30,601
And apologize for accusing me...

266
00:15:30,601 --> 00:15:32,661
of being nice to Seong Mi
just to get her blessing.

267
00:15:32,861 --> 00:15:35,931
- Dad, did you really say that?
- Dad, that was a bit out of line...

268
00:15:36,101 --> 00:15:38,201
Do you have any idea
what my life's been like?

269
00:15:38,471 --> 00:15:40,541
I've spent my entire life
giving in to you.

270
00:15:40,611 --> 00:15:42,741
I sacrificed it all for this family.
You get that?

271
00:15:42,871 --> 00:15:44,241
And why did you live like that?

272
00:15:44,511 --> 00:15:46,011
Just so you could hold it
over my head?

273
00:15:46,311 --> 00:15:50,221
- Holding it over your head? Really?
- Yes, that's exactly what it is.

274
00:15:50,821 --> 00:15:53,091
Hey, you punk.
If that's how you really feel,

275
00:15:53,391 --> 00:15:57,161
then don't you dare pretend to care
about my wife and kids! Got it?

276
00:15:57,261 --> 00:16:00,831
- Dad.
- Honey, that's enough. Please stop.

277
00:16:02,661 --> 00:16:05,001
How could you just trample all over
my sincere feelings like that?

278
00:16:05,101 --> 00:16:06,161
Sincere feelings?

279
00:16:06,601 --> 00:16:09,001
- Sincere feelings?
- Yes, sincere feelings!

280
00:16:09,471 --> 00:16:11,301
- Think you can just run your mouth?
- Dad, no.

281
00:16:11,301 --> 00:16:12,601
- Go on, hit me!
- No.

282
00:16:12,601 --> 00:16:14,471
- You punk! How dare you?
- Honey, please...

283
00:16:14,471 --> 00:16:16,381
- What? Sincere feelings?
- Dad, stop!

284
00:16:16,381 --> 00:16:18,241
- Hit me!
- I swear, this punk...

285
00:16:18,241 --> 00:16:19,241
No, stop...

286
00:16:28,551 --> 00:16:29,721
Did you hear all that?

287
00:16:32,291 --> 00:16:33,291
Yes.

288
00:16:34,391 --> 00:16:36,401
About Uncle, they broke up.

289
00:16:36,701 --> 00:16:38,601
He's just acting out
because he's heartbroken.

290
00:16:39,001 --> 00:16:41,901
Gosh, I don't get how...

291
00:16:41,901 --> 00:16:43,971
we got so tangled up
with that family.

292
00:16:44,741 --> 00:16:46,071
Tell me about it.

293
00:16:46,771 --> 00:16:49,171
It's so weird, isn't it?

294
00:16:50,411 --> 00:16:51,411
Ju Ah.

295
00:16:53,311 --> 00:16:54,411
You know,

296
00:16:55,681 --> 00:16:57,781
I feel like such a terrible person.

297
00:16:58,681 --> 00:17:00,751
No, you're not, Grandma.

298
00:17:02,891 --> 00:17:07,231
Both my son and my granddaughter
have found such great love.

299
00:17:08,261 --> 00:17:12,961
But instead of being happy for them,
I have to be the bad guy...

300
00:17:13,771 --> 00:17:15,171
I just wonder if anyone understands
how that feels.

301
00:17:17,001 --> 00:17:18,701
I'm sorry, Grandma.

302
00:17:24,581 --> 00:17:26,451
You were in the wrong.

303
00:17:26,911 --> 00:17:27,911
I know.

304
00:17:28,351 --> 00:17:30,821
If you knew you were wrong,
then why did you do that?

305
00:17:31,281 --> 00:17:32,821
I thought if I got mad,

306
00:17:34,391 --> 00:17:36,391
Mom might go a little easier on him.

307
00:17:39,761 --> 00:17:42,261
Still, you should apologize
to your brother tomorrow.

308
00:17:43,761 --> 00:17:45,401
Yes, I will.

309
00:17:46,971 --> 00:17:49,471
I just can't make sense
of any of this.

310
00:17:50,371 --> 00:17:54,111
I just hope the Yangs
never find out about this.

311
00:17:55,271 --> 00:17:56,371
Me, too.

312
00:17:56,711 --> 00:17:58,841
They won't get their blessing
anyway.

313
00:17:59,881 --> 00:18:02,511
Your brother will just get hurt
for nothing.

314
00:18:04,751 --> 00:18:06,721
That kid... Why her, of all people?

315
00:18:13,561 --> 00:18:14,961
Honestly, you're unbelievable.

316
00:18:15,331 --> 00:18:17,331
A private detective agency?
What were you thinking?

317
00:18:19,261 --> 00:18:22,471
Don't just sit there.
At least give Hyun Bin a call.

318
00:18:28,271 --> 00:18:32,141
- Oh, Se Ri! Have you been drinking?
- Yes, she's had a lot to drink.

319
00:18:33,011 --> 00:18:34,051
Let's go inside, Se Ri.

320
00:18:34,381 --> 00:18:35,651
Let go of me.

321
00:18:36,381 --> 00:18:37,481
Se Ri.

322
00:18:37,921 --> 00:18:40,021
Are you really going to let me in?
Aren't you too scared?

323
00:18:41,391 --> 00:18:45,091
You're so afraid
I'll steal your fortune.

324
00:18:45,591 --> 00:18:47,631
How are you going to sleep at night?

325
00:18:48,761 --> 00:18:52,031
Dad, I'll have her sleep
in Eun Bin's room tonight.

326
00:18:52,101 --> 00:18:53,331
- Yes, that's a better idea.
- Yes.

327
00:18:53,401 --> 00:18:55,731
Come on, Se Ri, let's go upstairs.
You can sleep with the girls.

328
00:18:55,871 --> 00:18:59,911
- Fine. I'll go upstairs.
- Let's go. Se Ri, be careful.

329
00:18:59,971 --> 00:19:00,971
Gosh, careful.

330
00:19:02,911 --> 00:19:03,911
Oh, gosh.

331
00:19:06,211 --> 00:19:07,381
Can't she try to understand?

332
00:19:11,481 --> 00:19:12,751
(Application for Divorce
by Mutual Consent)

333
00:19:14,721 --> 00:19:15,751
Darn...

334
00:19:16,761 --> 00:19:18,621
I must have been out of my mind,
seriously.

335
00:19:19,421 --> 00:19:21,431
Get a grip, you fool.

336
00:19:22,291 --> 00:19:24,001
How long will you keep this up?
Seriously.

337
00:19:25,361 --> 00:19:26,471
My gosh...

338
00:19:32,471 --> 00:19:34,971
What?
What did you want to talk about?

339
00:19:35,341 --> 00:19:36,411
You know,

340
00:19:37,711 --> 00:19:40,051
I heard about you and Uncle Dae Han.

341
00:19:42,151 --> 00:19:43,281
We're going to break up.

342
00:19:43,851 --> 00:19:45,421
I already told him it's over.

343
00:19:47,391 --> 00:19:51,121
Things are messy enough.
Let's not stir up more family drama.

344
00:19:52,521 --> 00:19:54,961
What are you guys talking about?

345
00:19:55,391 --> 00:19:57,961
Auntie, your boyfriend
was Woo Jae's uncle?

346
00:19:58,131 --> 00:20:01,031
- Hey, keep your voice down.
- My gosh.

347
00:20:01,401 --> 00:20:04,971
Auntie, are you out of your mind?
Grandpa and Dad will go crazy.

348
00:20:05,171 --> 00:20:06,271
I know.

349
00:20:06,341 --> 00:20:08,341
Mom would never approve of it
either.

350
00:20:08,411 --> 00:20:10,741
That's why Hyun Bin gave up
without even saying anything.

351
00:20:11,211 --> 00:20:14,111
- Eun Bin.
- What? What are you talking about?

352
00:20:15,051 --> 00:20:17,221
You dated Dr. Gong's daughter?

353
00:20:17,881 --> 00:20:19,051
We broke up.

354
00:20:19,351 --> 00:20:20,851
- For good?
- Yes.

355
00:20:20,951 --> 00:20:22,951
My goodness,
what kind of crazy mess is this?

356
00:20:23,291 --> 00:20:25,021
Eun Bin, you liked Woo Jae too,
didn't you?

357
00:20:25,091 --> 00:20:29,261
So we almost became triple in-laws,
not just double.

358
00:20:30,931 --> 00:20:34,001
Does that family know?
That you were dating their daughter?

359
00:20:34,731 --> 00:20:38,041
Only her grandmother knew,
and she was against it.

360
00:20:38,901 --> 00:20:41,041
Right. I figured she would be.

361
00:20:42,041 --> 00:20:43,511
That makes perfect sense.

362
00:21:22,981 --> 00:21:25,581
Why? Is today a special occasion?

363
00:21:26,521 --> 00:21:27,521
Tomorrow is.

364
00:21:28,121 --> 00:21:29,521
What's so special about tomorrow?

365
00:21:30,261 --> 00:21:31,561
Your grandmother...

366
00:21:32,891 --> 00:21:36,231
It's the 30th anniversary of the day
she ran off with another man.

367
00:21:54,011 --> 00:21:55,011
Gong Dae Han.

368
00:21:56,751 --> 00:21:58,981
- Hey, about yesterday, I was...
- Mom.

369
00:22:00,351 --> 00:22:01,491
Seong Mi, I...

370
00:22:02,491 --> 00:22:03,861
I'm going to move out.

371
00:22:04,891 --> 00:22:06,761
I'll call the clinic back
where I had an interview.

372
00:22:06,761 --> 00:22:08,291
If that doesn't work,
I'll find another.

373
00:22:09,731 --> 00:22:11,261
Then I'll look for a place to live
nearby.

374
00:22:11,661 --> 00:22:14,671
Are you saying
you're quitting the clinic, too?

375
00:22:14,971 --> 00:22:15,971
Yes, I am.

376
00:22:16,631 --> 00:22:18,141
Once you find my replacement,

377
00:22:18,141 --> 00:22:20,311
I'll get them up to speed
before I leave, so don't worry.

378
00:22:20,371 --> 00:22:23,171
- Gong Dae Han.
- Hey, are you really doing this?

379
00:22:23,411 --> 00:22:24,411
Dad.

380
00:22:24,941 --> 00:22:27,151
Uncle, you can't be serious.

381
00:22:27,651 --> 00:22:30,821
He's right, Dae Han.
Please reconsider.

382
00:22:31,081 --> 00:22:33,181
No, Seong Mi. I'm not a kid anymore.

383
00:22:33,591 --> 00:22:36,191
It's not right to still be living
with family at my age.

384
00:22:36,451 --> 00:22:39,761
And I know you're all embarrassed
that I'm divorced and living here.

385
00:22:40,391 --> 00:22:43,291
I'm no help around here,
so I'm just a burden on everyone.

386
00:22:43,831 --> 00:22:45,831
- Hey, you...
- You're right.

387
00:22:46,401 --> 00:22:47,931
I've thought about it,
and you were right about everything.

388
00:22:48,501 --> 00:22:51,471
I chose to make sacrifices
and then lorded it over everyone.

389
00:22:52,071 --> 00:22:55,971
So from now on,
I'm just going to live for myself.

390
00:22:56,371 --> 00:22:58,941
- Dae Han.
- I'm going to head to work.

391
00:22:59,311 --> 00:23:00,381
Make sure you finish your breakfast.

392
00:23:01,411 --> 00:23:04,121
- Dae Han...
- Hey, Dae Han! Hey, Gong Dae Han!

393
00:23:04,921 --> 00:23:05,951
Gosh, that guy...

394
00:23:14,461 --> 00:23:15,891
Father, these are...

395
00:23:16,291 --> 00:23:19,001
the deeds to the land
and buildings registered in my name.

396
00:23:20,831 --> 00:23:21,831
Why are you giving these to me?

397
00:23:22,971 --> 00:23:24,701
I can't accept these, Father.

398
00:23:26,271 --> 00:23:27,941
Accepting these...

399
00:23:28,311 --> 00:23:29,911
will make me look like a woman
who entered a beauty pageant...

400
00:23:29,911 --> 00:23:31,511
just to seduce a wealthy man
and change her life,

401
00:23:32,341 --> 00:23:35,551
a gold digger
stealing for her secret daughter.

402
00:23:36,281 --> 00:23:40,951
- Se Ri, don't be so dramatic.
- I came here with nothing,

403
00:23:41,591 --> 00:23:43,791
so I think it's only right
that I leave with nothing, Father.

404
00:23:44,621 --> 00:23:47,631
What...
Honey, what are you talking about?

405
00:23:48,961 --> 00:23:50,501
Are you asking for a divorce?

406
00:23:52,231 --> 00:23:54,101
You're the one who wants a divorce,
aren't you?

407
00:23:54,471 --> 00:23:56,401
I told you that's not it, Se Ri.

408
00:23:56,731 --> 00:23:59,241
I want you to consider it carefully
and then make your decision.

409
00:24:00,471 --> 00:24:02,571
Until you get your thoughts
straight,

410
00:24:03,041 --> 00:24:04,241
I'll be living somewhere else.

411
00:24:04,511 --> 00:24:07,581
You're moving out? You mean
you're planning to separate?

412
00:24:08,981 --> 00:24:10,921
Hyun Bin.

413
00:24:12,421 --> 00:24:14,591
I agree.
You two should take some time apart.

414
00:24:15,021 --> 00:24:17,591
You can stay at my place
for a while.

415
00:24:19,961 --> 00:24:20,961
Hey!

416
00:24:31,941 --> 00:24:35,011
I'm sorry for making this decision,
Father.

417
00:24:36,111 --> 00:24:38,781
Trust between a husband and wife
is more important than love.

418
00:24:40,081 --> 00:24:42,051
Just sweeping it under the rug
isn't the answer.

419
00:24:43,351 --> 00:24:46,381
Thank you for understanding, Father.

420
00:24:48,051 --> 00:24:52,021
Go and live on your own
until you're not so hurt anymore.

421
00:24:53,121 --> 00:24:54,131
Okay.

422
00:24:54,491 --> 00:24:57,931
But if you have no change of heart,
I...

423
00:24:58,501 --> 00:24:59,961
won't stand in your way.

424
00:25:01,571 --> 00:25:02,701
If, by any chance...

425
00:25:04,171 --> 00:25:06,271
If we really do get a divorce,

426
00:25:08,171 --> 00:25:12,211
I just took over the mattress store,
so I can't give it back right away.

427
00:25:12,611 --> 00:25:16,351
- I'll sort that out as things...
- That's yours to keep.

428
00:25:16,851 --> 00:25:21,451
All the years you ran this home.
A salary would be worth more.

429
00:25:24,991 --> 00:25:26,161
You need to...

430
00:25:27,261 --> 00:25:29,131
take care of your health, Father.

431
00:25:29,761 --> 00:25:31,501
Don't worry about things here.

432
00:25:32,201 --> 00:25:33,771
Go spend time with your daughter.

433
00:25:36,271 --> 00:25:37,341
I'm so sorry.

434
00:25:41,271 --> 00:25:42,971
This isn't like you.

435
00:25:43,341 --> 00:25:44,941
Don't you understand why I did it...

436
00:25:46,341 --> 00:25:48,411
Is this all of it?

437
00:25:49,281 --> 00:25:51,881
Yes. All my clothes were borrowed.

438
00:25:53,081 --> 00:25:54,191
I...

439
00:25:54,721 --> 00:25:58,061
never spent a single penny
on myself.

440
00:25:59,121 --> 00:26:02,631
I've never earned my own money,
so I have no savings either.

441
00:26:03,561 --> 00:26:04,561
Honey.

442
00:26:05,131 --> 00:26:06,301
Are you really going to do this?

443
00:26:07,231 --> 00:26:09,871
I don't want a divorce.
I'm not getting a divorce.

444
00:26:10,801 --> 00:26:11,801
I know.

445
00:26:12,401 --> 00:26:13,811
Of course, you don't want a divorce.

446
00:26:14,311 --> 00:26:17,141
You're still filming that show
and need the nomination.

447
00:26:17,681 --> 00:26:19,681
You can't afford a scandal.

448
00:26:20,451 --> 00:26:21,511
Se Ri.

449
00:26:22,151 --> 00:26:24,351
That's not what I meant.

450
00:26:24,451 --> 00:26:27,991
Even if we separate,
I'll make sure you're not affected.

451
00:26:28,491 --> 00:26:31,521
I'll play the supportive wife
in public until you make council.

452
00:26:32,261 --> 00:26:36,191
I want to do my part
to help you achieve your dream.

453
00:26:37,501 --> 00:26:38,661
Se Ri, please.

454
00:26:39,631 --> 00:26:40,971
I'll change, okay?

455
00:26:44,641 --> 00:26:45,741
Hey.

456
00:26:46,141 --> 00:26:49,041
- How can you be so irresponsible?
- What did I do?

457
00:26:49,111 --> 00:26:53,011
Why encourage them to separate
when you're about to leave?

458
00:26:53,181 --> 00:26:56,311
After you and Min Seo both take off,
what am I supposed to do by myself?

459
00:26:56,981 --> 00:26:59,651
It's up to them to figure it out.

460
00:27:01,691 --> 00:27:04,821
Don't say that.
Can't you stay a bit longer? Please?

461
00:27:04,991 --> 00:27:09,291
Can't you just not go? Besides,
you and Ju Ah broke up anyway.

462
00:27:09,561 --> 00:27:11,361
Do you really have to go?

463
00:27:14,001 --> 00:27:15,001
Hey.

464
00:27:19,641 --> 00:27:23,211
The Ceviel HR team.
They're intense, calling this early.

465
00:27:23,911 --> 00:27:25,211
Yes, this is Gong Ju Ah speaking.

466
00:27:26,341 --> 00:27:30,081
Yes. I understand.
I'll reply by the end of the week.

467
00:27:31,121 --> 00:27:33,921
Hey, "by the end of the week?"
Seriously?

468
00:27:35,091 --> 00:27:37,091
- Let's go grab some coffee.
- Hey!

469
00:27:41,731 --> 00:27:42,731
What's with you?

470
00:27:45,001 --> 00:27:46,061
What? It's Director Yang.

471
00:27:46,401 --> 00:27:48,571
- Hey, no!
- What? What's going on?

472
00:27:48,631 --> 00:27:49,701
Let's go someplace else.

473
00:27:50,031 --> 00:27:51,041
Wait a second.

474
00:27:51,471 --> 00:27:53,971
Hey, are you avoiding Director Yang?

475
00:27:56,011 --> 00:27:59,911
What happened to acting so cool?
Why the sudden change of heart?

476
00:28:00,141 --> 00:28:03,111
Gosh, I don't know. I just...
I can't face him all of a sudden.

477
00:28:07,651 --> 00:28:09,221
- Come on, let's go.
- For crying out loud...

478
00:28:09,751 --> 00:28:10,761
My gosh.

479
00:28:13,161 --> 00:28:16,231
The Claramont pop-up in Paris
is on hold?

480
00:28:16,891 --> 00:28:18,001
Yes.

481
00:28:18,301 --> 00:28:19,731
Stop messing with me.

482
00:28:20,631 --> 00:28:22,231
I'm regretting it now.

483
00:28:22,731 --> 00:28:24,471
Because my bluff actually came true.

484
00:28:28,071 --> 00:28:30,041
I'll go meet with Director Baek.
All right?

485
00:28:30,111 --> 00:28:32,841
We agreed not to interfere
with any ongoing contracts.

486
00:28:32,941 --> 00:28:34,681
What's to stop them
from going back on their word?

487
00:28:35,781 --> 00:28:37,551
There's an even bigger problem
than that.

488
00:28:37,821 --> 00:28:38,881
What is it?

489
00:28:40,021 --> 00:28:41,891
I think rumors are spreading
that your early exit...

490
00:28:41,891 --> 00:28:43,221
before the one-year contract ends...

491
00:28:43,621 --> 00:28:46,961
is due to concerns
about our brand's stability.

492
00:28:47,291 --> 00:28:48,531
What? So?

493
00:28:49,061 --> 00:28:51,061
Now, our other contracts
are starting to get shaky.

494
00:28:58,941 --> 00:29:01,671
I'm against the divorce. No way.

495
00:29:02,571 --> 00:29:04,441
I don't want
to get a divorce either.

496
00:29:05,011 --> 00:29:08,051
But I'm going to let
your father decide.

497
00:29:09,511 --> 00:29:10,651
Unbelievable.

498
00:29:11,751 --> 00:29:13,791
Maybe
I should just stay here with you.

499
00:29:14,291 --> 00:29:17,921
Why? Are you jealous that Mom and I
will have all the fun without you?

500
00:29:18,221 --> 00:29:22,831
No, I'm just sad
I won't spend more time with you.

501
00:29:23,161 --> 00:29:25,931
What? I'm actually really touched.

502
00:29:27,831 --> 00:29:30,971
In that case, Eun Bin,
until Min Seo leaves...

503
00:29:31,071 --> 00:29:32,301
Do you want to stay here with us?

504
00:29:35,311 --> 00:29:37,781
No, that's okay. I know you'd be
worried about Grandpa, Mom.

505
00:29:38,041 --> 00:29:40,651
I'll stay at the house
and make sure he eats well.

506
00:29:41,951 --> 00:29:44,051
Look at you.
When did you get so grown up?

507
00:29:44,821 --> 00:29:47,521
Just hurry up and get to work.
You're already cutting it close.

508
00:29:48,291 --> 00:29:49,691
Aren't you leaving?

509
00:29:49,991 --> 00:29:52,361
Oh, I have to be somewhere.

510
00:30:04,141 --> 00:30:08,341
Sorry for showing up unannounced.
You must be surprised.

511
00:30:09,041 --> 00:30:13,141
I was.
I was wondering why you're here.

512
00:30:15,151 --> 00:30:18,221
I know this is a lot to ask, but...

513
00:30:19,651 --> 00:30:23,861
Could you please convince my brother
not to leave?

514
00:30:25,191 --> 00:30:26,191
What?

515
00:30:26,521 --> 00:30:30,391
My brother was finally getting close
to our family.

516
00:30:30,831 --> 00:30:35,471
But if he leaves again like this,
I'm afraid we won't see him again.

517
00:30:37,901 --> 00:30:39,601
And also...

518
00:30:39,871 --> 00:30:44,241
Our family is going through a lot
right now.

519
00:30:46,641 --> 00:30:50,521
We need him here
to get us through this crisis.

520
00:30:55,391 --> 00:30:56,391
Well...

521
00:30:57,051 --> 00:30:58,721
I know it's incredibly hard for you.

522
00:30:59,891 --> 00:31:02,561
That it's uncomfortable
being around him,

523
00:31:03,291 --> 00:31:07,131
and that you're upset because
your heart races when you see him.

524
00:31:08,231 --> 00:31:09,631
I get all of that.

525
00:31:11,701 --> 00:31:12,801
Yes, you're right.

526
00:31:13,671 --> 00:31:14,911
But still,

527
00:31:15,541 --> 00:31:17,311
in time,

528
00:31:17,841 --> 00:31:20,141
I think it will get easier.

529
00:31:28,651 --> 00:31:29,951
The global contract.

530
00:31:30,351 --> 00:31:33,191
If it's on hold or falls through,
we lose our funding, right?

531
00:31:33,931 --> 00:31:37,531
Because of those rumors,
new orders have also dried up.

532
00:31:37,601 --> 00:31:39,061
This is really unsettling.

533
00:31:40,101 --> 00:31:42,931
The plan to expand the brand
to all Hyegyeong branches...

534
00:31:42,931 --> 00:31:44,501
isn't going to fall through, is it?

535
00:31:44,741 --> 00:31:47,371
Why would you say that?
Don't jinx it.

536
00:31:47,471 --> 00:31:49,771
It might, if they see
other failed contracts...

537
00:31:49,771 --> 00:31:51,111
as a red flag.

538
00:31:51,681 --> 00:31:53,381
We can't let that happen.

539
00:31:54,311 --> 00:31:56,751
Everyone, let's not get rattled.

540
00:31:56,851 --> 00:31:58,751
At a time like this,
we need to focus...

541
00:31:58,821 --> 00:32:00,481
and make sure
the production goes smoothly.

542
00:32:00,821 --> 00:32:04,891
So, should we move forward
with Hyegyeong's product assortment?

543
00:32:04,961 --> 00:32:05,961
Yes.

544
00:32:06,491 --> 00:32:08,091
All right, everyone, back to work.

545
00:32:08,591 --> 00:32:09,591
- Yes.
- Yes.

546
00:32:17,201 --> 00:32:18,201
Go ahead and check what you need to.

547
00:32:18,201 --> 00:32:21,411
Okay.
I'll review them all together later.

548
00:32:21,471 --> 00:32:23,211
- Can you also check...
- Hey, Nurse Oh.

549
00:32:23,211 --> 00:32:26,141
- Yes?
- About Mr. Park's manual therapy,

550
00:32:26,211 --> 00:32:29,211
we need to proceed conservatively,
focusing on pain relief.

551
00:32:29,351 --> 00:32:31,221
Could you please tell Mr. Gong?

552
00:32:32,021 --> 00:32:34,791
What? Wait, why are you asking me
to do that?

553
00:32:35,391 --> 00:32:36,551
Nurse Oh.

554
00:32:37,021 --> 00:32:41,131
Tell Dr. Gong I'll revise the plan
according to his feedback.

555
00:32:41,231 --> 00:32:43,231
Why are you both telling me to...

556
00:32:48,101 --> 00:32:49,831
My gosh...

557
00:32:54,171 --> 00:32:56,911
I'm worried this is going to drive
a wedge between the brothers.

558
00:32:58,111 --> 00:33:01,651
- The things we do for love...
- Well, love is important.

559
00:33:02,811 --> 00:33:05,021
- Right.
- Yes.

560
00:33:06,681 --> 00:33:08,891
- Hello.
- Hi, welcome.

561
00:33:09,121 --> 00:33:10,121
Hey, Mr. Gong!

562
00:33:10,391 --> 00:33:11,461
Oh, Officer Jung.

563
00:33:11,621 --> 00:33:13,291
If you're here alone,
care to join us?

564
00:33:15,091 --> 00:33:16,091
Is that okay?

565
00:33:16,561 --> 00:33:18,261
You already asked him.

566
00:33:19,301 --> 00:33:22,271
If I say no now,
I'm the one who looks bad.

567
00:33:22,531 --> 00:33:24,801
So you don't want us
to sit together?

568
00:33:25,271 --> 00:33:27,471
Forget it.
It's a little late for that.

569
00:33:29,641 --> 00:33:30,941
Please, sit here, Mr. Gong.

570
00:33:31,611 --> 00:33:33,211
I'll have an order
of the cockles, please.

571
00:33:33,711 --> 00:33:34,811
Yes, coming right up.

572
00:33:35,381 --> 00:33:38,121
Really, I would have been fine
on my own. But thanks.

573
00:33:38,221 --> 00:33:39,251
Oh, come on.

574
00:33:45,861 --> 00:33:46,861
What are you looking at
so intensely?

575
00:33:47,361 --> 00:33:49,391
What?
I'm looking for a place to live.

576
00:33:49,731 --> 00:33:50,731
I'm going to move out.

577
00:33:51,401 --> 00:33:53,001
Come on. That's extreme.

578
00:33:53,461 --> 00:33:55,071
Are you really going to
go through with that?

579
00:33:56,131 --> 00:33:58,541
Any neighborhoods
you're thinking of?

580
00:33:59,271 --> 00:34:00,501
Around the Onjeong Intersection.

581
00:34:01,441 --> 00:34:05,541
Not there. Try the residential area
behind the post office.

582
00:34:05,911 --> 00:34:07,451
The security deposit there is
20,000 dollars,

583
00:34:07,751 --> 00:34:09,611
and rent starts at around
600 to 700 dollars a month.

584
00:34:10,781 --> 00:34:12,021
For every additional 10,000
in deposit,

585
00:34:12,021 --> 00:34:13,251
the rent is reduced by 50 dollars.

586
00:34:13,651 --> 00:34:15,121
Plus, it's a great area
with a lot of amenities.

587
00:34:17,251 --> 00:34:18,991
Wow, how do you know all of this?

588
00:34:19,191 --> 00:34:22,691
I'll move when I get married,
so I did my homework.

589
00:34:25,401 --> 00:34:26,401
What?

590
00:34:26,661 --> 00:34:29,871
You're already thinking
about marrying me?

591
00:34:30,331 --> 00:34:32,571
Well, isn't that a given?

592
00:34:35,311 --> 00:34:36,411
Yes, it is.

593
00:34:37,381 --> 00:34:38,411
You have to be that committed.

594
00:34:43,581 --> 00:34:45,081
Enjoy your meal.

595
00:34:46,281 --> 00:34:48,921
Looks like
you're busy with your date.

596
00:34:49,051 --> 00:34:51,691
Oh, we just had lunch together,
that's all.

597
00:34:52,521 --> 00:34:54,561
You knew, didn't you?

598
00:34:55,291 --> 00:34:56,631
Dae Han's girlfriend.

599
00:34:58,701 --> 00:34:59,761
Yes, I knew.

600
00:35:00,771 --> 00:35:02,931
But I didn't want to be the one
to tell you.

601
00:35:03,471 --> 00:35:05,241
Because I knew you two
would be so against it.

602
00:35:05,471 --> 00:35:08,041
- Good grief, you...
- Dr. Gong.

603
00:35:08,411 --> 00:35:12,411
Mr. Gong is looking for a house
and is even checking job listings.

604
00:35:13,211 --> 00:35:15,951
Can't you just turn a blind eye
and give them your blessing?

605
00:35:16,151 --> 00:35:17,651
Hey, Nurse Oh.

606
00:35:19,021 --> 00:35:21,591
Honestly,
I know it's not my place, but...

607
00:35:22,121 --> 00:35:25,291
If it's something from 30 years ago,
isn't that ancient history?

608
00:35:29,931 --> 00:35:30,961
I'm sorry.

609
00:35:31,831 --> 00:35:33,501
I crossed a line again.

610
00:35:40,341 --> 00:35:41,811
It was a long time ago.

611
00:35:42,611 --> 00:35:45,011
But I just can't seem to forget it.

612
00:35:47,081 --> 00:35:49,851
Even a physical wound can fester
if it's severe.

613
00:35:50,921 --> 00:35:53,851
So how could a wound to the heart
possibly have an expiration date?

614
00:35:54,851 --> 00:35:56,121
The pain just stays with you.

615
00:35:57,821 --> 00:35:59,821
Does Dr. Yang's family know?

616
00:36:00,491 --> 00:36:02,531
No, I don't think so.

617
00:36:04,301 --> 00:36:05,301
For the time being,

618
00:36:06,301 --> 00:36:09,431
don't say anything to Dae Han.
Got it?

619
00:36:09,731 --> 00:36:10,901
Okay, I won't.

620
00:36:12,071 --> 00:36:13,801
Where did he run off to now?

621
00:36:14,411 --> 00:36:16,471
Don't tell me
he's with Dong Suk again.

622
00:36:17,441 --> 00:36:18,481
- Like this.
- Yes.

623
00:36:18,541 --> 00:36:19,941
- Shoulders down.
- Okay.

624
00:36:19,941 --> 00:36:22,481
Yes. Okay,
stand up a little straighter.

625
00:36:22,681 --> 00:36:24,011
Okay, now for your arms...

626
00:36:24,381 --> 00:36:26,821
- Keep them close to your body.
- Right.

627
00:36:26,881 --> 00:36:30,251
Rotate your wrists slowly like this,
five times.

628
00:36:30,451 --> 00:36:32,091
That's it. Slowly. One, two,

629
00:36:32,661 --> 00:36:35,631
- Three...
- three, four, five.

630
00:36:36,131 --> 00:36:38,001
You don't have to push yourself.
Take it slow, okay?

631
00:36:39,261 --> 00:36:41,371
Starting next week,
we'll slowly add shoulder exercises.

632
00:36:41,831 --> 00:36:42,831
Okay.

633
00:36:43,471 --> 00:36:44,471
Dae Han.

634
00:36:46,041 --> 00:36:47,441
You don't have to go through
all this trouble...

635
00:36:47,941 --> 00:36:49,771
to help me.

636
00:36:52,781 --> 00:36:55,081
This is a promise I made, so...

637
00:36:55,581 --> 00:36:57,281
I'm not looking for credit,
Seong Mi.

638
00:36:57,481 --> 00:37:00,721
I know. How could I not?

639
00:37:01,321 --> 00:37:03,051
I'm glad you understand, Seong Mi.

640
00:37:03,691 --> 00:37:05,321
Are you really going to move out?

641
00:37:06,261 --> 00:37:07,361
You don't even have any money.

642
00:37:08,231 --> 00:37:09,731
I'll stay at the clinic
for the time being.

643
00:37:10,291 --> 00:37:14,371
I should get back to work.
Keep your arms close when rotating.

644
00:37:14,601 --> 00:37:16,071
- Okay.
- All right.

645
00:37:20,341 --> 00:37:21,841
(3H Acupressure Bed)

646
00:37:22,911 --> 00:37:24,011
Yes, Sister.

647
00:37:24,811 --> 00:37:26,241
She's grown up so well.

648
00:37:27,711 --> 00:37:31,351
Yes, we'll visit you together
before Veronica leaves for the US.

649
00:37:32,181 --> 00:37:33,181
All right.

650
00:37:33,251 --> 00:37:35,191
(3H Acupressure Bed)

651
00:37:35,291 --> 00:37:37,521
I bet the Sister was overjoyed.

652
00:37:37,821 --> 00:37:40,891
Yes. She says you're a miracle,

653
00:37:41,191 --> 00:37:43,091
a gift that found its way to me.

654
00:37:45,131 --> 00:37:48,901
Right! My mom in the US said
she wants to talk to you, too.

655
00:37:49,271 --> 00:37:50,271
Really?

656
00:37:51,301 --> 00:37:52,771
That makes me a little nervous.

657
00:37:53,641 --> 00:37:55,671
Do I have to speak English?
I'm not very good at it.

658
00:37:57,071 --> 00:37:58,711
You can just speak Korean.

659
00:38:00,011 --> 00:38:02,711
If you're too nervous now,
we can always do it later.

660
00:38:02,981 --> 00:38:06,581
Yes. When I feel I'm ready,

661
00:38:07,051 --> 00:38:09,191
- I'll let you know then.
- Okay.

662
00:38:09,651 --> 00:38:11,761
I'm just going to pop over
to the stationery store out front.

663
00:38:11,961 --> 00:38:13,061
Okay, go ahead.

664
00:38:17,131 --> 00:38:18,131
Welcome.

665
00:38:19,231 --> 00:38:20,231
Here for the beds?

666
00:38:22,271 --> 00:38:23,701
Well...

667
00:38:24,841 --> 00:38:26,241
Sorry to make you come
all the way here.

668
00:38:26,641 --> 00:38:29,541
Not at all.
I was planning to visit you anyway.

669
00:38:29,611 --> 00:38:31,781
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

670
00:38:31,841 --> 00:38:33,441
This...

671
00:38:34,881 --> 00:38:35,981
No, I can't.

672
00:38:35,981 --> 00:38:38,121
Grandpa already gave me
pocket money.

673
00:38:38,521 --> 00:38:40,781
It's not pocket money. It's a bribe.

674
00:38:42,821 --> 00:38:45,121
Put in a good word for me
with your mother.

675
00:38:47,161 --> 00:38:48,161
Okay.

676
00:38:48,831 --> 00:38:49,931
When you smile,

677
00:38:50,291 --> 00:38:52,161
you really do look
a lot like my Se Ri.

678
00:38:53,431 --> 00:38:54,871
Though, Se Ri is a little prettier,
of course.

679
00:38:56,131 --> 00:38:59,401
Gosh, this is so awkward,
I'm just saying strange things.

680
00:39:00,071 --> 00:39:01,071
You know how it is.

681
00:39:02,041 --> 00:39:05,411
I'm sorry.
You're even separated because of me.

682
00:39:05,911 --> 00:39:08,881
No. It's my fault. I deserve it.

683
00:39:09,511 --> 00:39:12,581
I have absolutely no intention
of divorcing Se Ri,

684
00:39:13,181 --> 00:39:15,591
- so don't you worry.
- I'm not worried.

685
00:39:16,121 --> 00:39:17,291
Watching you two,

686
00:39:17,761 --> 00:39:19,091
I can tell how you feel
about each other.

687
00:39:19,991 --> 00:39:21,761
You're smart, just like Se Ri.

688
00:39:22,791 --> 00:39:24,961
You go to Johns Hopkins, right?

689
00:39:25,401 --> 00:39:26,401
Yes.

690
00:39:27,361 --> 00:39:28,371
I'm so glad to finally meet you.

691
00:39:29,371 --> 00:39:32,701
I always wondered what it'd be like
to have a daughter like Se Ri.

692
00:39:33,571 --> 00:39:37,511
And wow, just like that,
a grown daughter drops from the sky.

693
00:39:37,571 --> 00:39:38,741
I'm still a bit bewildered, but...

694
00:39:39,511 --> 00:39:41,711
I really mean it.
I'm so happy to have you.

695
00:39:42,451 --> 00:39:44,651
Thank you for welcoming me.

696
00:39:46,781 --> 00:39:48,821
Even after you go back,

697
00:39:49,421 --> 00:39:51,291
come visit us again anytime.

698
00:39:51,891 --> 00:39:54,831
- Can I really?
- Of course.

699
00:39:56,191 --> 00:39:58,001
This is your home.

700
00:39:58,661 --> 00:39:59,801
We're your family.

701
00:40:01,371 --> 00:40:02,571
Thank you.

702
00:40:06,401 --> 00:40:07,641
Easy does it.

703
00:40:08,911 --> 00:40:12,441
You need to start walking a little
to get your strength back, okay?

704
00:40:13,411 --> 00:40:15,081
Let's walk together every day.

705
00:40:15,781 --> 00:40:16,781
Should we?

706
00:40:16,851 --> 00:40:19,821
Yes. Tomorrow, let's go out
for a walk around the neighborhood.

707
00:40:22,021 --> 00:40:23,151
Oh, wait.

708
00:40:23,791 --> 00:40:25,921
- Oh, no. My goodness.
- Hold on.

709
00:40:31,231 --> 00:40:34,631
You're so sweet to me.
It feels like we're dating again.

710
00:40:35,531 --> 00:40:36,801
Oh, really?

711
00:40:37,531 --> 00:40:38,601
In that case...

712
00:40:38,971 --> 00:40:41,271
Maybe we could
push our beds back together?

713
00:40:42,911 --> 00:40:44,841
Sure, I guess.

714
00:40:45,581 --> 00:40:46,581
What?

715
00:40:47,141 --> 00:40:48,781
Wait, did you just say yes? Did you?

716
00:40:48,911 --> 00:40:50,511
I'm going to push them together
the second we get inside.

717
00:40:53,281 --> 00:40:55,751
You know, about Dae Han...

718
00:40:56,551 --> 00:40:58,791
Why don't we let him do
as he pleases?

719
00:40:59,791 --> 00:41:01,461
What? What are you talking about?

720
00:41:01,831 --> 00:41:03,891
Were there strings attached
to pushing our beds together?

721
00:41:04,461 --> 00:41:07,801
Honestly, it's not really
our decision to make, is it?

722
00:41:08,171 --> 00:41:11,871
You're right. What can I do?
He's a grown man.

723
00:41:12,441 --> 00:41:14,001
I'm just a little worried about Mom.

724
00:41:15,841 --> 00:41:17,981
But I think Dae Han...

725
00:41:18,281 --> 00:41:20,941
is really into Bucket's sister.

726
00:41:21,181 --> 00:41:23,481
Yes, he's always had
a thing for her.

727
00:41:23,951 --> 00:41:26,151
Really? Was she his first love?

728
00:41:27,451 --> 00:41:30,151
It was probably a one-sided crush
on Dae Han's part.

729
00:41:30,521 --> 00:41:32,421
Dong Suk was really popular,
you know?

730
00:41:32,721 --> 00:41:35,091
But she married the wrong guy
and had a really hard time.

731
00:41:35,691 --> 00:41:36,831
Well...

732
00:41:37,591 --> 00:41:40,461
Should I try talking
to Mother about it?

733
00:41:42,331 --> 00:41:44,771
Sure. Go ahead if you want to.

734
00:41:47,471 --> 00:41:48,811
I'm washing my hands of this.

735
00:41:56,451 --> 00:41:57,651
What did you want to talk about?

736
00:41:58,281 --> 00:42:03,021
- I was just bored.
- Come on. Who are you fooling?

737
00:42:05,561 --> 00:42:07,461
I wanted to talk about Dae Han.

738
00:42:09,231 --> 00:42:11,731
I'm sorry he's got you this worried
when you're sick.

739
00:42:12,501 --> 00:42:14,701
This is just between you and me,
Mother.

740
00:42:15,271 --> 00:42:16,731
I feel alive.

741
00:42:17,531 --> 00:42:21,241
- What?
- I specialize in family problems.

742
00:42:21,811 --> 00:42:25,111
Now that I'm facing conflict,
my instincts are kicking in.

743
00:42:25,341 --> 00:42:26,441
I love it.

744
00:42:28,781 --> 00:42:30,151
That's a relief.

745
00:42:31,551 --> 00:42:34,351
Go on then. Present your solution.

746
00:42:35,921 --> 00:42:40,221
Let me get a free consultation
from the famous Dr. Han Seong Mi.

747
00:42:41,661 --> 00:42:44,191
It's not that I don't understand
how you feel, Mother.

748
00:42:44,731 --> 00:42:47,031
It's not easy for me
to bring this up, either.

749
00:42:47,731 --> 00:42:48,731
I know.

750
00:42:50,071 --> 00:42:51,071
I also...

751
00:42:51,901 --> 00:42:53,741
could use an objective conversation.

752
00:42:55,171 --> 00:42:58,681
I was so against Ju Ah
and Director Yang,

753
00:42:58,681 --> 00:43:00,081
so you probably don't understand
why I'm like this...

754
00:43:00,481 --> 00:43:01,611
when it comes to Dae Han.

755
00:43:02,751 --> 00:43:03,851
Seong Mi.

756
00:43:04,821 --> 00:43:07,081
It's probably because
you care so much about Dae Han.

757
00:43:08,291 --> 00:43:09,291
Yes.

758
00:43:09,621 --> 00:43:12,561
He's older now,
and he's been hurt before.

759
00:43:13,591 --> 00:43:17,391
And it won't be easy
for him to meet someone new.

760
00:43:21,371 --> 00:43:22,471
You know, Dae Han...

761
00:43:30,911 --> 00:43:33,041
He understands me
better than anyone.

762
00:43:34,611 --> 00:43:36,381
After his father left us,

763
00:43:38,351 --> 00:43:41,021
while you and Jeong Han
were busy studying,

764
00:43:42,051 --> 00:43:43,721
right after he got out of the army,

765
00:43:44,551 --> 00:43:46,021
he looked after
his niece and nephew,

766
00:43:47,061 --> 00:43:48,991
and he stayed by my side,
protecting me.

767
00:43:50,991 --> 00:43:52,001
I know.

768
00:43:52,361 --> 00:43:53,501
Back then,

769
00:43:54,901 --> 00:43:58,041
I cried
and felt resentment every day,

770
00:43:58,641 --> 00:44:00,271
and I was filled with rage
every day.

771
00:44:02,071 --> 00:44:03,411
Without you kids knowing,

772
00:44:04,311 --> 00:44:06,481
all the private anguish
I went through...

773
00:44:07,741 --> 00:44:09,351
Dae Han saw it all.

774
00:44:11,651 --> 00:44:12,681
But...

775
00:44:16,251 --> 00:44:19,161
for me to still be acting like this
after 30 years...

776
00:44:21,491 --> 00:44:23,791
Dae Han must be
very disappointed in me.

777
00:44:30,001 --> 00:44:33,101
What about getting a divorce?

778
00:44:37,341 --> 00:44:38,981
So Dr. Han Seong Mi's solution...

779
00:44:39,481 --> 00:44:40,481
is a divorce?

780
00:44:41,651 --> 00:44:45,821
Your negative feelings about
what's happening with Dae Han...

781
00:44:46,821 --> 00:44:49,791
I think it's less about the present
and more about Father...

782
00:44:50,251 --> 00:44:52,921
and your unresolved feelings
from the past.

783
00:44:53,891 --> 00:44:57,831
A divorce would help resolve
your resentment and anger,

784
00:44:59,061 --> 00:45:01,671
weakening their hold on you.

785
00:45:01,901 --> 00:45:05,441
You'd likely see Dae Han's situation
in a new light.

786
00:45:09,341 --> 00:45:10,341
Mother.

787
00:45:13,981 --> 00:45:14,981
You're right.

788
00:45:15,851 --> 00:45:17,151
It's long overdue,

789
00:45:18,721 --> 00:45:20,021
but I think
that's what I have to do.

790
00:45:33,501 --> 00:45:35,001
I'm so sorry, Ms. Na.

791
00:45:36,271 --> 00:45:38,701
I should have known better.

792
00:45:39,371 --> 00:45:41,641
Dae Han is such a good man,

793
00:45:42,911 --> 00:45:44,411
and I got greedy.

794
00:45:45,811 --> 00:45:46,981
Does your family...

795
00:45:47,911 --> 00:45:48,911
know about you two?

796
00:45:49,981 --> 00:45:50,981
No.

797
00:45:56,621 --> 00:45:58,121
One day, out of the blue,

798
00:45:59,321 --> 00:46:01,061
my kids' father disappeared.

799
00:46:02,561 --> 00:46:04,831
He rushed out late one night,
saying he had to see a patient,

800
00:46:05,501 --> 00:46:06,931
and then I just lost contact
with him.

801
00:46:08,801 --> 00:46:12,441
I was worried he had an accident,
so I searched for him frantically.

802
00:46:13,641 --> 00:46:15,311
I was grabbing anyone I could find
in the neighborhood...

803
00:46:16,411 --> 00:46:18,281
and asking if they'd seen him.

804
00:46:19,481 --> 00:46:20,481
But the way people...

805
00:46:21,011 --> 00:46:23,311
looked at me was strange.

806
00:46:25,151 --> 00:46:26,821
So when I asked why,

807
00:46:28,591 --> 00:46:29,721
they told me they saw my husband...

808
00:46:31,021 --> 00:46:34,961
embracing your mother.
That's what they said.

809
00:46:37,661 --> 00:46:38,831
Your mom and I...

810
00:46:39,501 --> 00:46:42,101
You remember how close we were,
don't you?

811
00:46:43,231 --> 00:46:44,231
Yes.

812
00:46:47,101 --> 00:46:50,471
Your mother and my husband
are still out there living together,

813
00:46:51,611 --> 00:46:53,611
so if you and Dae Han live together,

814
00:46:54,611 --> 00:46:56,351
it would just be too weird.

815
00:46:58,181 --> 00:46:59,251
On top of that,

816
00:47:00,351 --> 00:47:03,621
people will never stop talking about
your ex-spouses.

817
00:47:04,321 --> 00:47:05,321
And you'll probably...

818
00:47:06,821 --> 00:47:09,131
face judgment from people...

819
00:47:09,931 --> 00:47:11,731
for the rest of your lives.

820
00:47:18,301 --> 00:47:19,301
Can you handle that?

821
00:47:20,641 --> 00:47:21,641
Even with all that,

822
00:47:22,711 --> 00:47:24,371
can you still love Dae Han?

823
00:47:27,381 --> 00:47:28,381
Pardon?

824
00:47:29,311 --> 00:47:30,311
As for me,

825
00:47:30,851 --> 00:47:32,751
I want to let Dae Han
do whatever he wants.

826
00:47:33,581 --> 00:47:34,821
I'm going to stay out of it.

827
00:47:40,491 --> 00:47:43,431
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

828
00:47:43,491 --> 00:47:44,491
Dong Suk.

829
00:47:47,231 --> 00:47:48,571
What are you doing here?

830
00:47:49,331 --> 00:47:50,331
What?

831
00:47:50,671 --> 00:47:52,571
It's just...
I feel more comfortable here.

832
00:47:53,201 --> 00:47:54,201
Go home.

833
00:47:55,041 --> 00:47:56,041
Dong Suk.

834
00:47:57,511 --> 00:47:59,341
Your mom came to see me.

835
00:48:01,011 --> 00:48:03,411
What did she say?
What did my mom say now?

836
00:48:04,581 --> 00:48:05,981
She said we can do whatever we want.

837
00:48:07,221 --> 00:48:08,251
Really?

838
00:48:09,991 --> 00:48:12,491
She gave us her blessing? For real?

839
00:48:12,821 --> 00:48:14,821
- For real?
- Dae Han.

840
00:48:15,391 --> 00:48:16,831
What? Why? Aren't you happy?

841
00:48:17,531 --> 00:48:19,461
She didn't give us her blessing.

842
00:48:20,131 --> 00:48:21,131
She's given up on us.

843
00:48:21,301 --> 00:48:23,201
No. She gave us her blessing.

844
00:48:24,031 --> 00:48:25,901
Let's move away and live together,
just the two of us.

845
00:48:26,141 --> 00:48:27,141
Dae Han.

846
00:48:28,341 --> 00:48:29,341
We should...

847
00:48:33,041 --> 00:48:34,581
just end things, okay?

848
00:48:36,611 --> 00:48:37,611
Dong Suk, why?

849
00:48:38,751 --> 00:48:42,251
I feel like I've just been
giving you false hope.

850
00:48:44,191 --> 00:48:45,191
Dong Suk, I...

851
00:48:46,921 --> 00:48:49,261
Stop pushing me away.
If you keep this up...

852
00:48:49,961 --> 00:48:51,061
I'm going to lose all hope.

853
00:48:51,731 --> 00:48:54,031
No. I just...

854
00:48:54,461 --> 00:48:55,601
can't do this.

855
00:48:57,371 --> 00:49:00,941
I can't bear to see you
put your family through this.

856
00:49:01,771 --> 00:49:03,211
You don't really mean that.

857
00:49:03,471 --> 00:49:05,511
I know how precious
your family is to you.

858
00:49:07,011 --> 00:49:08,141
I've already made up my mind.

859
00:49:08,481 --> 00:49:09,481
No.

860
00:49:10,211 --> 00:49:11,451
No. For me...

861
00:49:12,421 --> 00:49:13,621
I can't accept that.

862
00:49:16,691 --> 00:49:19,721
The thought of you cutting ties
with your family to be with me...

863
00:49:20,691 --> 00:49:21,691
I can't stand it.

864
00:49:39,641 --> 00:49:41,751
Pacu Nacho, are you off work?

865
00:49:42,251 --> 00:49:45,281
Yes. I'm on my way
to my parents' place. What's up?

866
00:49:46,981 --> 00:49:49,391
What? Who's resigning?

867
00:49:51,551 --> 00:49:53,121
This is some gentle skincare.

868
00:49:53,391 --> 00:49:55,261
I put some in the bathroom
just for you.

869
00:49:55,761 --> 00:49:57,291
Oh, thanks.

870
00:49:59,261 --> 00:50:00,261
Mom.

871
00:50:00,561 --> 00:50:01,731
I need to talk to you
about something.

872
00:50:02,201 --> 00:50:03,201
What is it?

873
00:50:03,731 --> 00:50:05,241
I've been recruited,

874
00:50:05,571 --> 00:50:06,641
and I'm thinking of
changing companies.

875
00:50:08,341 --> 00:50:12,581
My FG collection you modeled for
was a big success.

876
00:50:13,041 --> 00:50:14,581
I'm telling you because...

877
00:50:14,581 --> 00:50:17,211
I was worried you'd be upset
if I left the company.

878
00:50:19,221 --> 00:50:23,391
Director Yang is quitting
and going back to Argentina, I hear?

879
00:50:24,421 --> 00:50:27,391
Gosh, what does Director Yang
have to do with this?

880
00:50:27,891 --> 00:50:30,391
I saw a clip of your interview
earlier.

881
00:50:32,701 --> 00:50:37,001
For your mom to walk the runway
wearing the clothes you designed...

882
00:50:37,701 --> 00:50:42,411
- Wow, that must've been so special.
- My lifelong dream came true.

883
00:50:44,071 --> 00:50:46,441
- "Lifelong dream," my foot.
- The show's concept...

884
00:50:46,441 --> 00:50:49,251
was both modern and luxurious,
which I found very impressive.

885
00:50:49,751 --> 00:50:53,381
Was there anyone in particular
who inspired this collection?

886
00:50:54,181 --> 00:50:57,721
If you can't say who, could you just
tell us a little about them?

887
00:50:59,061 --> 00:51:01,791
He's the one who made it possible
for me to become a designer.

888
00:51:02,061 --> 00:51:04,031
He opened up a whole new world
for me.

889
00:51:05,701 --> 00:51:09,631
So that people could find happiness
wearing the clothes I designed,

890
00:51:10,001 --> 00:51:13,101
he was always by my side,
thinking things through with me,

891
00:51:13,871 --> 00:51:16,211
and kept me grounded.

892
00:51:21,481 --> 00:51:24,411
And? What about it?

893
00:51:24,881 --> 00:51:26,121
You were talking about
Director Yang, weren't you?

894
00:51:28,251 --> 00:51:32,491
- Did Grandma tell you?
- No, I figured it out on my own.

895
00:51:32,761 --> 00:51:33,761
My gosh.

896
00:51:34,491 --> 00:51:36,691
We broke up,
so you don't have to worry about it.

897
00:51:38,461 --> 00:51:39,461
Tell me.

898
00:51:40,501 --> 00:51:43,631
Did you break up with him
because I hate his mother?

899
00:51:43,731 --> 00:51:44,731
Well...

900
00:51:45,501 --> 00:51:47,171
That's part of it, but...

901
00:51:47,741 --> 00:51:51,411
I broke up with him. I didn't think
I could handle everything.

902
00:51:52,881 --> 00:51:54,941
I don't want to see him...

903
00:51:55,411 --> 00:51:57,751
separated from his family
because of me.

904
00:51:58,481 --> 00:52:01,821
To keep Director Yang
from going back to Argentina,

905
00:52:02,921 --> 00:52:04,351
I guess I'm the one
who has to leave.

906
00:52:07,791 --> 00:52:10,191
You really can't stand to work
at the same company?

907
00:52:12,231 --> 00:52:13,231
No.

908
00:52:13,831 --> 00:52:16,771
If I see him, I don't think
I'll be able to let go.

909
00:52:18,971 --> 00:52:20,501
Then quit.

910
00:52:21,271 --> 00:52:22,441
Change companies.

911
00:52:23,141 --> 00:52:24,141
Okay.

912
00:52:38,421 --> 00:52:40,361
Did you resign because of me?

913
00:52:42,961 --> 00:52:46,631
No. I just accepted another offer.

914
00:52:46,901 --> 00:52:50,031
But why so suddenly? What about FG?

915
00:52:50,531 --> 00:52:55,041
Right now, FG needs you, not me.

916
00:52:58,941 --> 00:52:59,941
Ju Ah.

917
00:53:04,911 --> 00:53:08,021
Stay with your family.
Don't go back to Argentina.

918
00:53:09,121 --> 00:53:11,521
You need your family.

919
00:53:12,961 --> 00:53:16,061
The thought of you being separated
from your family because of me...

920
00:53:17,031 --> 00:53:18,491
I don't think I could bear it.

921
00:53:19,601 --> 00:53:21,131
So, working together
at the same company...

922
00:53:21,971 --> 00:53:23,031
Is that really not an option?

923
00:53:25,471 --> 00:53:26,471
No.

924
00:53:50,591 --> 00:53:51,831
(My Dr. Yang)

925
00:54:00,401 --> 00:54:02,371
Hey, Se Ri, it's me.

926
00:54:03,011 --> 00:54:04,011
Yes.

927
00:54:06,281 --> 00:54:09,251
You're staying there
starting tonight, right?

928
00:54:10,211 --> 00:54:11,451
Is something wrong at home?

929
00:54:11,921 --> 00:54:12,921
No.

930
00:54:13,621 --> 00:54:14,981
Then why did you call?

931
00:54:15,351 --> 00:54:16,451
No reason.

932
00:54:17,091 --> 00:54:18,421
I'm going to hang up then.

933
00:54:22,531 --> 00:54:24,691
You could've been a little nicer.

934
00:54:25,261 --> 00:54:26,731
I wish I could.

935
00:54:27,261 --> 00:54:28,771
But I'm doing this on purpose.

936
00:54:30,031 --> 00:54:34,041
If I just let this slide,
he'll never be able to trust me.

937
00:54:35,371 --> 00:54:36,371
Let's eat.

938
00:54:36,711 --> 00:54:37,711
Okay.

939
00:55:10,411 --> 00:55:12,511
You said today was your last shoot,
right?

940
00:55:13,611 --> 00:55:14,611
Yes.

941
00:55:14,941 --> 00:55:17,511
I was so sick of pretending
to be friends with Bucket,

942
00:55:17,981 --> 00:55:19,051
and now it's finally over.

943
00:55:19,751 --> 00:55:20,751
By the way,

944
00:55:21,051 --> 00:55:24,821
is Uncle really staying
at the clinic?

945
00:55:29,131 --> 00:55:30,391
Well, actually...

946
00:55:32,801 --> 00:55:33,901
Woo Jae.

947
00:55:34,531 --> 00:55:35,531
What's wrong?

948
00:55:36,301 --> 00:55:37,301
What is it?

949
00:55:38,671 --> 00:55:41,441
Well, the thing is...

950
00:55:42,641 --> 00:55:47,141
Uncle asked me to bring him a suit,
so I just dropped it off for him.

951
00:55:47,711 --> 00:55:49,151
A suit? Why all of a sudden?

952
00:55:49,611 --> 00:55:53,451
He said he'll face them head-on
before he gives up.

953
00:55:55,051 --> 00:55:56,121
What did you say?

954
00:55:59,391 --> 00:56:00,391
Unbelievable.

955
00:56:19,041 --> 00:56:20,041
It's today, isn't it?

956
00:56:21,241 --> 00:56:22,681
The day Mom left home.

957
00:56:23,211 --> 00:56:25,651
Forget it. Why would you remember
something like that?

958
00:56:26,721 --> 00:56:27,881
How could I forget?

959
00:56:28,791 --> 00:56:29,791
How's Se Ri?

960
00:56:30,191 --> 00:56:31,421
She's doing fine with Min Seo.

961
00:56:32,521 --> 00:56:33,921
After my last shoot today,

962
00:56:34,821 --> 00:56:36,031
I'll go and check on her again.

963
00:56:42,401 --> 00:56:43,471
Uncle Dae Han.

964
00:56:54,281 --> 00:56:55,951
Hello, sir, Dong Ik.

965
00:56:56,551 --> 00:56:58,781
What the... What are you doing here?

966
00:56:59,751 --> 00:57:02,121
I've come to ask
for your permission.

967
00:57:02,621 --> 00:57:04,491
Permission for what?

968
00:57:14,261 --> 00:57:15,401
Sir, Dong Ik.

969
00:57:16,471 --> 00:57:17,471
I, Gong Dae Han,

970
00:57:18,301 --> 00:57:19,371
am in love with your daughter,

971
00:57:21,141 --> 00:57:22,671
Yang Dong Suk.

972
00:57:23,371 --> 00:57:24,371
What?

973
00:57:24,871 --> 00:57:26,741
Please give me your permission
to date Dong Suk.

974
00:57:27,881 --> 00:57:30,081
- Mom.
- What's wrong?

975
00:57:30,351 --> 00:57:32,451
- Hurry.
- Why? What's going on?

976
00:57:33,221 --> 00:57:34,721
Hey, what the heck
is he talking about?

977
00:57:35,591 --> 00:57:36,591
What?

978
00:57:36,921 --> 00:57:38,321
If you would both give me
your blessing,

979
00:57:39,091 --> 00:57:40,191
I'd like to spend my life
with Dong Suk...

980
00:57:41,191 --> 00:57:43,091
and build a happy future together.

981
00:57:43,331 --> 00:57:46,561
- What in the world is...
- Hey!

982
00:57:47,561 --> 00:57:49,031
This guy must be crazy.

983
00:57:50,531 --> 00:57:51,531
Dong Ik!

984
00:57:52,141 --> 00:57:53,141
Father.

985
00:57:53,871 --> 00:57:56,341
Hey, what is he talking about?

986
00:57:57,011 --> 00:57:59,711
- It's nothing. It's really nothing.
- Hey!

987
00:58:00,511 --> 00:58:01,941
Is Gong Dae Han your boyfriend?

988
00:58:02,281 --> 00:58:03,451
- Yes, that's right.
- No...

989
00:58:04,281 --> 00:58:05,481
Dong Suk's boyfriend...

990
00:58:06,651 --> 00:58:07,651
That's me.

991
00:58:08,891 --> 00:58:10,591
What is this absolute nonsense?

992
00:58:10,821 --> 00:58:12,521
Grandpa.

993
00:58:12,791 --> 00:58:14,691
- I need your blessing, Father.
- You punk!

994
00:58:14,691 --> 00:58:18,331
- Get out! Get out of here now!
- Grandpa, you should go inside.

995
00:58:18,331 --> 00:58:20,631
I'm not taking a step out of here
until you give me your blessing!

996
00:58:21,361 --> 00:58:22,401
You son of a...

997
00:58:23,201 --> 00:58:24,571
- You jerk.
- Dong Ik!

998
00:58:24,571 --> 00:58:26,101
Hey, how dare you?

999
00:58:26,101 --> 00:58:28,241
- Get out, you punk!
- Stop!

1000
00:58:28,801 --> 00:58:30,271
Don't you dare treat him like that.

1001
00:58:31,441 --> 00:58:32,441
For crying out loud.

1002
00:58:32,741 --> 00:58:34,281
Have these two completely
lost their minds?

1003
00:58:34,881 --> 00:58:35,951
Hey, Gong Dae Han.

1004
00:58:36,411 --> 00:58:39,281
Is this why you were so nice to me
this whole time?

1005
00:58:39,721 --> 00:58:40,921
Yes, that's right, Dong Ik.

1006
00:58:41,651 --> 00:58:42,791
I'm in love with Dong Suk,

1007
00:58:43,121 --> 00:58:44,691
and I was trying to get
your blessing.

1008
00:58:45,051 --> 00:58:46,061
Hey.

1009
00:58:46,391 --> 00:58:49,191
Are you pretending you don't know
who Mom left us for?

1010
00:58:49,491 --> 00:58:51,691
What do your brother and your mother
have to say about this?

1011
00:58:51,691 --> 00:58:54,031
- How can you think this is okay?
- So what?

1012
00:58:54,431 --> 00:58:57,501
- Who cares? That's all in the past!
- What did you just say?

1013
00:58:57,501 --> 00:59:00,241
I pursued him.
I'm the one who said I liked him!

1014
00:59:00,941 --> 00:59:03,371
What do I care about the past?
I love him!

1015
00:59:04,011 --> 00:59:06,081
So don't you dare blame
Dae Han for this!

1016
00:59:08,511 --> 00:59:09,781
Dae Han, go.

1017
00:59:10,881 --> 00:59:12,481
You don't have to stand here
and take this.

1018
00:59:13,421 --> 00:59:16,591
Yes, go on. Get out!
Get out of here, you punk!

1019
00:59:16,991 --> 00:59:19,421
No. I'm not leaving.

1020
00:59:20,021 --> 00:59:22,931
- Has that punk lost his mind?
- I am not leaving.

1021
00:59:23,661 --> 00:59:25,901
- Grandpa.
- You jerk, shut your mouth!

1022
00:59:25,961 --> 00:59:27,961
- I won't! I can't!
- How...

1023
00:59:28,561 --> 00:59:29,931
I live for Dong Suk.

1024
00:59:29,931 --> 00:59:31,571
She's my everything.
You got a problem with that?

1025
00:59:31,831 --> 00:59:33,071
I told you to shut it, you punk!

1026
00:59:33,141 --> 00:59:36,241
No! No matter how much you object,
I'm going to be with Dong Suk.

1027
00:59:36,241 --> 00:59:38,211
Dong Suk, Ji Hu, and me!

1028
00:59:40,141 --> 00:59:41,411
We want to be happy.
What's wrong with that?

1029
00:59:42,551 --> 00:59:45,721
You. I told you to shut your mouth.

1030
00:59:45,921 --> 00:59:48,351
- You son of a...
- Please leave. Go!

1031
00:59:49,391 --> 00:59:50,491
Stop it, Dae Han.

1032
00:59:51,191 --> 00:59:52,621
You've done enough.

1033
00:59:53,661 --> 00:59:55,161
Let's just stop this.

1034
00:59:57,061 --> 00:59:58,061
Dong Suk!

1035
00:59:59,931 --> 01:00:01,001
I love you!

1036
01:00:02,031 --> 01:00:03,071
You love her?

1037
01:00:03,371 --> 01:00:06,101
Go love your own mother, you punk!
How dare you say that here?

1038
01:00:06,471 --> 01:00:09,611
Hey. If I ever see you
with Dong Suk again,

1039
01:00:09,971 --> 01:00:12,111
I'll kill you with my own two hands.
Got it?

1040
01:00:13,241 --> 01:00:15,811
And don't bring this garbage
into my house ever again!

1041
01:00:53,921 --> 01:00:54,921
Jeong Han.

1042
01:00:58,521 --> 01:00:59,961
Happy now?

1043
01:01:00,561 --> 01:01:01,791
Got that out of your system?

1044
01:01:11,801 --> 01:01:12,841
Jeong Han...

1045
01:01:14,301 --> 01:01:15,301
Hey, you fool.

1046
01:01:16,271 --> 01:01:19,881
This is why I tried to stop you,
you punk.

1047
01:01:24,081 --> 01:01:25,311
I can't believe this kid.

1048
01:01:43,371 --> 01:01:45,031
How could you all do this to me?

1049
01:01:46,471 --> 01:01:47,601
I'm sorry, Dad.

1050
01:01:48,141 --> 01:01:49,141
You...

1051
01:01:49,611 --> 01:01:54,541
Are you so blinded by a man
that I mean nothing to you?

1052
01:01:55,341 --> 01:01:57,151
Of all the men in the world,

1053
01:01:58,051 --> 01:01:59,951
you give your heart to him?

1054
01:02:01,821 --> 01:02:04,321
I'm sorry. I won't see him again.

1055
01:02:05,961 --> 01:02:07,791
From now on,
I'll live as if I were dead.

1056
01:02:08,821 --> 01:02:09,831
Grandpa.

1057
01:02:11,831 --> 01:02:12,961
Is it really impossible?

1058
01:02:13,331 --> 01:02:14,331
Impossible.

1059
01:02:15,201 --> 01:02:19,171
Over my dead body. Got it?

1060
01:02:47,431 --> 01:02:51,971
<i>On our different paths in life</i>

1061
01:02:52,441 --> 01:02:57,841
<i>We've wandered for far too long</i>

1062
01:02:59,241 --> 01:03:04,851
<i>Never knowing our hearts were closed</i>

1063
01:03:05,311 --> 01:03:09,651
<i>All we did was resent each other</i>

1064
01:03:11,121 --> 01:03:13,791
<i>- Today is the day</i>
<i>- Today is the day</i>

1065
01:03:13,791 --> 01:03:16,961
<i>- We become a family again</i>
<i>- We become a family again</i>

1066
01:03:17,031 --> 01:03:19,561
<i>- A precious day</i>
<i>- A precious day</i>

1067
01:03:19,561 --> 01:03:23,331
<i>- Though long overdue</i>
<i>- Though long overdue</i>

1068
01:03:23,971 --> 01:03:30,211
<i>- Let's live our lives with love</i>
<i>- Let's live our lives with love</i>

1069
01:03:33,081 --> 01:03:34,141
(Live Singing Performance
to Energize You)

1070
01:03:34,141 --> 01:03:35,411
Cut!

1071
01:03:35,781 --> 01:03:39,281
- Hey, that was a great take!
- Yes. Thank you.

1072
01:03:39,281 --> 01:03:41,881
Let's take a short break,
then shoot the examination.

1073
01:03:41,951 --> 01:03:44,251
- Sure, got it.
- All right.

1074
01:03:44,251 --> 01:03:45,691
Hey, spare me a minute.

1075
01:03:47,061 --> 01:03:48,061
Yes.

1076
01:03:51,591 --> 01:03:55,031
(Onjeong Village Hall)

1077
01:03:55,101 --> 01:03:56,101
Hey.

1078
01:03:58,131 --> 01:03:59,171
Did you know or not?

1079
01:04:00,071 --> 01:04:03,071
- What?
- About your brother and my sister.

1080
01:04:03,311 --> 01:04:05,711
They're not together anymore,
so just drop it.

1081
01:04:05,881 --> 01:04:09,081
Love? You've got to be kidding me.
What's love? What do they know?

1082
01:04:09,511 --> 01:04:10,511
Listen here.

1083
01:04:10,981 --> 01:04:13,251
If that punk sees my sister
one more time,

1084
01:04:13,681 --> 01:04:15,281
I'll kill that Gong Dae Han myself.

1085
01:04:15,351 --> 01:04:18,621
Go ahead and try it.
You do, and I'll kill you.

1086
01:04:18,951 --> 01:04:21,991
Have you no pride? Grow up.

1087
01:04:22,631 --> 01:04:24,991
Look, whatever.
Now that the shoot is over,

1088
01:04:25,161 --> 01:04:27,201
let's keep out of
each other's lives. Got it?

1089
01:04:27,361 --> 01:04:29,061
That's my line!

1090
01:04:30,801 --> 01:04:31,971
Hello, this is Yang Dong Ik.

1091
01:04:33,201 --> 01:04:35,571
I'm sorry, who? Gu In Ok?

1092
01:04:38,871 --> 01:04:41,581
Yes, Gu In Ok is my mother. Why?

1093
01:04:44,751 --> 01:04:46,121
What did you just say?

1094
01:04:47,281 --> 01:04:48,351
My mother...

1095
01:04:49,791 --> 01:04:51,091
What did you say happened to her?

1096
01:05:21,951 --> 01:05:24,521
(Recipe For Love)

1097
01:05:24,591 --> 01:05:27,991
He gave me the kind of love
I'd never gotten from anyone else.

1098
01:05:27,991 --> 01:05:30,491
Let's forget it all and have fun,
the three of us.

1099
01:05:30,491 --> 01:05:33,501
Wow, thanks to my girls,
I'm trying so many new things.

1100
01:05:33,831 --> 01:05:35,261
Today, I'm going to do
whatever I want.

1101
01:05:35,761 --> 01:05:39,071
I regret it. It's all my fault.

1102
01:05:39,301 --> 01:05:40,971
She's in critical condition.

1103
01:05:40,971 --> 01:05:44,011
They called Dr. Yang's family
to the hospital.

1104
01:05:44,111 --> 01:05:46,081
I found my mom.

1105
01:05:50,006 --> 01:05:52,006
Dramaday.me
